# Tyre Management System - Master Plan & Implementation Sequence

## **Application Structure & Page Hierarchy**

### **Main Navigation Structure:**

```
Dashboard (Home)
├── Inventory Management
│   ├── Tyre Registry
│   │   ├── Add New Tyre
│   │   ├── Edit Tyre Details
│   │   ├── View Tyre History
│   │   └── Tyre Search/Filter
│   ├── Vehicle Management
│   │   ├── Vehicle List
│   │   ├── Add/Edit Vehicle
│   │   └── Vehicle-Tyre Assignment
│   └── Stock Management
│       ├── Current Stock
│       ├── Purchase Orders
│       └── Stock Transfers
├── Operations
│   ├── Installation/Removal
│   │   ├── New Installation
│   │   ├── Tyre Rotation
│   │   └── Removal Records
│   ├── Inspections
│   │   ├── Schedule Inspection
│   │   ├── Inspection Checklist
│   │   └── Inspection History
│   └── Maintenance
│       ├── Service Requests
│       ├── Repair Logs
│       └── Retreading Records
├── Monitoring & Alerts
│   ├── Active Alerts
│   ├── Alert Configuration
│   └── Notification Settings
├── Analytics & Reports
│   ├── Dashboard
│   ├── Cost Reports
│   ├── Performance Reports
│   └── Compliance Reports
├── Administration
│   ├── User Management
│   ├── Role Permissions
│   ├── System Settings
│   └── Audit Logs
└── Help & Support
    ├── User Guide
    ├── FAQ
    └── Contact Support
```

## **Detailed Page Requirements**

### **Phase 1: POC Pages (Weeks 1-4)**

#### **1. Dashboard Page**
```
URL: /dashboard
Purpose: Overview of tyre status and key metrics
Components:
- Summary cards: Total Tyres, Active, In Stock, Scrapped
- Upcoming maintenance alerts (next 7 days)
- Recent installations/removals
- Quick action buttons
```

#### **2. Tyre Registry Page**
```
URL: /tyres
Purpose: Central repository of all tyres
Components:
- Search/Filter panel (by ID, status, vehicle)
- Tyre list table with key details
- Action buttons: Add, Edit, View Details
- Status badges (color-coded)
- Export to CSV/PDF option
```

#### **3. Add/Edit Tyre Page**
```
URL: /tyres/add, /tyres/edit/:id
Purpose: Create/Update tyre information
Fields:
- Basic: Tyre ID (auto/manual), Brand, Model, Size, Type
- Purchase: Date, Cost, Supplier, Warranty details
- Specifications: Load Index, Speed Rating, Tread Depth (new)
- Initial Status: New/Used/Retread
```

#### **4. Tyre Detail Page**
```
URL: /tyres/view/:id
Purpose: Complete tyre history and details
Components:
- Basic info card
- Current status and location
- Installation history timeline
- Maintenance records
- Cost tracking summary
```

#### **5. Vehicle Management Page**
```
URL: /vehicles
Purpose: Manage fleet vehicles
Components:
- Vehicle list with details
- Add/Edit vehicle forms
- Tyre assignment modal/popup
- Vehicle-wise tyre position view
```

#### **6. Installation/Removal Page**
```
URL: /operations/install
Purpose: Track tyre assignments
Components:
- Vehicle selection
- Tyre selection (from available stock)
- Position selection (Front/Rear + Left/Right/Center)
- Odometer reading input
- Technician/Operator details
```

#### **7. Reports Page (Basic)**
```
URL: /reports/basic
Purpose: Simple analytics
Components:
- Cost overview chart
- Tyre lifespan statistics
- Wear rate summary
```

---

### **Phase 2: Must-Have Features Pages (Weeks 5-12)**

#### **8. Advanced Tyre Lifecycle Page**
```
URL: /lifecycle/:id
Purpose: Detailed audit trail
Components:
- Timeline visualization
- State transition history
- Document attachments
- Approval workflow (if needed)
```

#### **9. Maintenance Scheduling Page**
```
URL: /maintenance/schedule
Purpose: Automated service management
Components:
- Calendar view of scheduled maintenance
- Rule-based scheduling setup
- Reminder configuration
- Inspection templates
```

#### **10. Inspection Module Pages**
```
URL: /inspections
Sub-pages:
- /inspections/schedule (Create new)
- /inspections/checklist/:id (Perform inspection)
- /inspections/history (View past inspections)
- /inspections/templates (Manage templates)
```

#### **11. Cost Management Pages**
```
URL: /costs
Sub-pages:
- /costs/depreciation (Calculations)
- /costs/repairs (Tracking)
- /costs/analysis (TCO reports)
- /costs/comparison (Brand/model comparison)
```

#### **12. Advanced Reporting Pages**
```
URL: /reports
Sub-pages:
- /reports/wear-analysis
- /reports/performance
- /reports/compliance
- /reports/custom (Report builder)
```

#### **13. User Management Pages**
```
URL: /admin/users
Sub-pages:
- /admin/users/list (Manage users)
- /admin/roles (Role permissions)
- /admin/audit-logs (Activity tracking)
- /admin/settings (System configuration)
```

---

## **Implementation Sequence & Timeline**

### **Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1-2)**
**Week 1: Core Setup**
1. Project setup & database schema
2. Authentication system
3. Basic dashboard layout
4. Navigation structure

**Week 2: Tyre Registry**
1. Tyre CRUD operations
2. Search & filter functionality
3. Status management
4. Basic dashboard metrics

### **Phase 2: Core Functionality (Week 3-4)**
**Week 3: Vehicle & Assignment**
1. Vehicle management
2. Installation tracking
3. Position management
4. Odometer tracking

**Week 4: Basic Analytics & POC Completion**
1. Mileage calculations
2. Basic cost tracking
3. Simple reports
4. POC testing & feedback

### **Phase 3: Must-Have Features (Week 5-8)**
**Week 5: Lifecycle Management**
1. Complete audit trail
2. State transitions
3. History tracking
4. Document management

**Week 6: Maintenance System**
1. Scheduling engine
2. Alert system
3. Inspection templates
4. Checklist management

### **Phase 4: Advanced Features (Week 9-12)**
**Week 7: Cost Management**
1. Depreciation models
2. Repair cost tracking
3. TCO calculations
4. Budgeting tools

**Week 8: Reporting Engine**
1. Report templates
2. Export functionality
3. Visualization charts
4. Scheduled reports

**Week 9: User Management**
1. Role-based access
2. Permission matrix
3. Audit logging
4. System settings

### **Phase 5: Polish & Deployment (Week 10-12)**
**Week 10: Integration & API**
1. External system APIs
2. Data import/export
3. Mobile responsiveness
4. Performance optimization

**Week 11: Testing & QA**
1. User acceptance testing
2. Bug fixes
3. Performance testing
4. Security review

**Week 12: Deployment & Training**
1. Production deployment
2. User training materials
3. Documentation
4. Support setup

